<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer5151419852550357598">JC Lamont is a literary apologist and historian specializing in Second Temple Judaism and Early Christianity. She is a student of Koine Greek, and a former contributor for the Christian Apologetics Alliance. She hosts an online chronological Bible Study, Blogging His Story, a nonfiction companion to The Chronicles of Time series.<br/><br/> Now broken into four, full-length novels, Volume I, <a href='https://www.amazon.com/Prophecy-Heir-Primordium-Chronicles-Time-ebook/dp/B07LB5XW2L' rel='nofollow noopener'>Prophecy of the </a></span>
  <span id="freeText5151419852550357598" style="display:none">JC Lamont is a literary apologist and historian specializing in Second Temple Judaism and Early Christianity. She is a student of Koine Greek, and a former contributor for the Christian Apologetics Alliance. She hosts an online chronological Bible Study, Blogging His Story, a nonfiction companion to The Chronicles of Time series.<br /><br /> Now broken into four, full-length novels, Volume I, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Prophecy-Heir-Primordium-Chronicles-Time-ebook/dp/B07LB5XW2L" rel="nofollow noopener">Prophecy of the Heir</a>, won the 2007 FaithWriters Page Turner Competition, and covers from creation through the birth of Christ through the eyes of Michael the archangel. A student of Koine Greek, JC is currently working on Volumes II and III of The Chronicles of Time series.</span>
